header.gameNote: OHIO VALLEY CONF TR AT EASTERN KENTUCKY

article.headline: E. Kentucky 63, Morehead St. 45
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. (AP) -- Jamaal Douglas scored 16 points as Eastern Kentucky beat Morehead State 63-45 Tuesday night in the first round of the Ohio Valley Conference tournament. Mike Rose and Julian Mascoll added 11 points each for Eastern (19-11). Rose scored all his points in the first half. Cordaryl Ballard led Morehead (12-17) with 17 points and Quentin Pryor followed with 11. The Colonels advanced to the conference semifinals for the first time in two years and will take on Tennessee Tech on Friday in Nashville, Tenn. Tennessee Tech defeated Southeast Missouri State 88-60 in a first-round game Tuesday. Eastern never trailed and put the game away with a 16-0 run in the first half, turning a 9-8 lead into a 25-8 advantage with 6:45 left in the half. The Colonels, who shot 62.5 percent from the field in the first half, hit four 3-pointers during the decisive spurt, and they finished with eight for the game. The Colonels led by 26 with eight minutes left in the second half, and the Eagles couldn't get any closer than 13.
